{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a331dbbd-79bc-4026-b525-4576666afd2d","content":"In **.NET 10 SDK**, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform — you **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was the opt-in bridge for .NET 9 SDK; in .NET 10 it's the default behavior.\n\nYou can simply remove that line:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```\n\nYour project already has `EnableMSTestRunner` set to `true`, which produces the MTP-based executable host. With .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` will automatically discover and run it via MTP without any additional opt-in.\n\n**TL;DR for your .csproj:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThat's all you need. Would you like me to update the file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"66588c48-e2e2-4c80-a1ef-1be9672fd39a","outputTokens":264,"requestId":"680A:2CF0DF:733344:7AB6EC:6A044DC1"},"id":"73d0cd25-e492-446b-8a78-3e65897729b2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:09:12.130Z","parentId":"a43d1e81-90e8-48f3-adaf-5d44036a651e"}
